					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What mapper would you recommend?
<br />I was just reading the docs and the BANDAI mapper (mapper 16) looks great! It is really simple, lets you swap small chunks of VROM, has IRQ's... I just fell in love with the thing! But I guess it isn't one of the most populars, right? I think FCEUltra doesn't even support it, does it?
<br />
<br />What should I have in mind when choosing a mapper? Unfortunately I have no way of testing my programs/demos/games on the real hardware, so I shouldn't worry about having a cartrige with the same mapper. Or should I, on the remote possibility of getting my program/game/demo ever placed on the real thing?
<br />
<br />I'd like to choose a simple mapper, but the simpler ones only swap BIG chunks of VROM, and my programs really need small swaps. And I'm not in the mood of replicating data and making lots of 8k chunks to simulate small swaps, and end up with a huge rom. Or using VRAM, what would be very sloooow...
<br />
<br />Well, what have you guys been using lately?</div>

